Package polyglot.types

Class Type_c

java.lang.Object
polyglot.types.TypeObject_c
polyglot.types.Type_c
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Qualifier, Type, TypeObject, Copy<TypeObject>
Direct Known Subclasses:
FunctionType_c, NullType_c, PrimitiveType_c, ReferenceType_c, UnknownType_c
public abstract class Type_c
extends TypeObject_c
implements Type
Abstract implementation of a Type. This implements most of the "isa" and "cast" methods of the type and methods which just dispatch to the type system.

    • toString

      public abstract java.lang.String toString()
      Description copied from interface: Type
      Yields a string representing this type. The string should be consistent with equality. That is, if this.equals(anotherType), then it should be that this.toString().equals(anotherType.toString()). The string is not necessarily a legal type expression in the language, such as a Java identifier. It is suggested, but not required, that it be an easily human-readable representation that can be used both in error messages and in generated output.
      Specified by:
      toString in interface Type
      Overrides:
      toString in class java.lang.Object

    • print

      public void print​(CodeWriter w)
      Output a compilable representation of this type to w. This implementation generates whatever representation is produced by toString(). To satisfy the specification of Type.toString(), this implementation needs to be overridden if toString does not produce a compilable representation.
      Specified by:
      print in interface Type
